post_text:
Dear South Central Stakeholders and Community:

Our school’s reopening plan for the 2020-2021 school year was approved by the Board of School Trustees at their regularly scheduled meeting this evening. Included in this post is a two-page at-a-glance summary of the plan. More detailed plans and a letter from our superintendent will be e-mailed to all parents / guardians and is available on our website: www.scentral.k12.in.us

As of today, South Central Schools is planning for 100% physical attendance at school on August 12th under the “YELLOW” category of the plan. A virtual learning option is available for any student who wishes to participate that way. More information will be sent out regarding the registration process for the upcoming school year.

We thank you for your patience and support as we navigate through these difficult times together.
text:
Dear South Central Stakeholders and Community:

Our school’s reopening plan for the 2020-2021 school year was approved by the Board of School Trustees at their regularly scheduled meeting this evening. Included in this post is a two-page at-a-glance summary of the plan. More detailed plans and a letter from our superintendent will be e-mailed to all parents / guardians and is available on our website: www.scentral.k12.in.us

As of today, South Central Schools is planning for 100% physical attendance at school on August 12th under the “YELLOW” category of the plan. A virtual learning option is available for any student who wishes to participate that way. More information will be sent out regarding the registration process for the upcoming school year.

We thank you for your patience and support as we navigate through these difficult times together.

Next week is Teacher Appreciation Week and even though we can't celebrate with our teachers in person, we still want to show them our appreciation. We've decorated our windows with hearts, Easter eggs, and more. Let's add to our decorations and show our love for our teachers. That way all the teachers can enjoy it even if they can't drive around. Let's spread this throughout the community. Show your Satellite Pride!

post_text: The 2020-21 Student Council application process begins this Monday, April 20. Any SC students going into 7th-12th grade next school year may apply. A Google Form application will be shared with the students in their Google Drive on Monday. Applications are due Friday, May 1. After that date, teachers will vote for their top 6 choices in each grade level. The top 6 students of each grade level will become members of the 2020-2021 South Central Student Council, pending good standing with grades, school behavior, and any previous Student Council involvement.

From PreK: Shiloh’s hero is his grandma Lori. She is a nurse at St. Joseph hospital in Michigan. She has been working 12 hour shifts 6 days a week in the midst of this chaos. A true hero in our eyes! Shiloh is on the left and his cousin Kaeson is on the right.

Brantley says his healthcare hero is his mom, Heather Harman. She has been a diagnostic medical sonographer (ultrasound) for Methodist hospital in Merrilliville and Gary for a year now and a pharmacy technician for CVS in Laporte for over 8 years.

Here is Maya Corley with her dad. He is working hard enforcing laws during quarantine and also doing security at Saint Anthony's Hospital.

shared_text:
Harold Welter is with Ben Anderson.
April 2 at 2:09 PM ·

The Cheryl Lyn Welter Charitable Foundation awarded 3 grants to South Central Schools to help with student distance learning through these difficult times. High School Principal Ben Anderson accepted the awards on behalf of Jr./Sr. High School Teacher Katie Etheridge and Elementary Teacher Amy Morrison. The grants will be used to provide books which the students can use at home, art supplies which they need to continue art e-learning at home and providing internet services for underprivileged students who don't otherwise have access to e-learning at home.
If you would like to help Teachers like these provide e-learning opportunities now that traditional school has been cancelled for the year, you may send your contribution by texting CHERYL to 71777.
The Need is Great...
The Solution is Love...
The Inspiration is Cheryl...
